<p class="nsw-docs__pattern-swatch-note">Reference swatches only. Use similar pattern density and scale in production charts, then validate at 200 percent zoom and at mobile widths. Pattern stroke is chosen to maintain minimum 3 to 1 non-text contrast.</p>

<h5>Implementation approach</h5>
<ul>
  <li>DDS does not prescribe a specific charting library, SVG pattern library or reusable pattern utility for canvas charts.</li>
  <li>Use any implementation approach that produces clear patterns and meets accessibility requirements.</li>
  <li>Examples on this page use pattern assets from <a target="_blank" href="https://patterns.helloyes.dev/">patterns.helloyes.dev</a>.</li>
</ul>

<h5>Usage in charts</h5>
<ul>
  <li>Do not pattern every series in a chart.</li>
  <li>Apply patterns selectively where colour and lightness alone are not enough to distinguish data.</li>
  <li>Avoid placing multiple series with similar colours and similar pattern density directly beside each other.</li>
</ul>

<h5>Colour blindness checks</h5>
<ul>
  <li>Test charts in greyscale and with colour-vision deficiency simulation (deuteranopia, protanopia and tritanopia).</li>
  <li>Confirm key insights are still clear without colour.</li>
  <li>If interpretation remains ambiguous, add direct labels and provide a semantic data table.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Keyboard access</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Interactive charts must support full keyboard operation (WCAG 2.1.1).</li>
  <li>All interactive elements are focusable with logical tab order.</li>
  <li>Visible focus indicators must not be hidden or obscured (WCAG 2.4.11).</li>
  <li>Interactive targets are at least 24 by 24 pixels (WCAG 2.5.8).</li>
  <li>Test keyboard interaction manually.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Text alternatives</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Provide a semantic data table.</li>
  <li>Provide a short summary of the key insight where appropriate.</li>
  <li>The data table must reflect the same dataset as the chart.</li>
  <li>Static image exports without alternatives are not acceptable.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Zoom and responsiveness</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Charts must remain usable at 200 percent zoom and at 375 pixel viewport width.</li>
  <li>Labels do not overlap.</li>
  <li>Primary information remains visible.</li>
  <li>Horizontal scrolling does not hide critical data.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Tool limitations</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Some third-party tools may restrict accessibility customisation.</li>
  <li>If a tool cannot meet WCAG requirements, document the limitation and provide an accessible alternative where possible.</li>
  <li>Accessibility responsibility remains with the product team.</li>
</ul>


<h2 id="brand-and-typography">Brand and typography</h2>
<p>Apply NSW brand colour and typography with care. Prioritise contrast and readability, and do not use the palette decoratively.</p>

<h3>Selecting colour for your charts</h3>
<p>Apply colours from your main colour theme first. If additional colours are required, they can be drawn from the wider colour palette.</p>

<h3>Applying brand with structure</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Use NSW Brand colour and typography intentionally.</li>
  <li>Use consistent shade rows across series to improve readability.</li>
  <li>Keep only what matters by limiting the number of data series.</li>
</ul>


<h2 id="tool-configuration">Tool configuration</h2>
<p>DDS does not prescribe tools. Tool defaults are not automatically compliant.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Apply the official NSW chart theme where available.</li>
  <li>Override default colour and typography settings.</li>
  <li>Test accessibility in the rendered environment.</li>
  <li>If a tool cannot meet requirements, provide an alternative.</li>
  <li>Consider accessibility capability when selecting vendors.</li>
</ul>


<h2 id="examples">Examples</h2>
<p>These examples show common issues and better implementations. Use them to spot risks early and improve consistency.</p>

<h3>Example 1: Truncated axis and unclear labels</h3>
<div class="nsw-grid nsw-m-top-sm">
  <div class="nsw-col nsw-col-sm-6 nsw-docs__guideline">
    <div class="nsw-docs__guideline--dont">Don't</div>
    <p>Column chart starts at 90, labels are rotated and the title does not explain the timeframe.</p>
    <div class="nsw-m-top-sm">
      <canvas id="example1Bad" height="180" role="img" aria-label="Column chart with truncated axis and rotated labels."></canvas>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li>Exaggerates differences by truncating the axis.</li>
      <li>Missing units and time period.</li>
      <li>Long labels are hard to read.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="nsw-col nsw-col-sm-6 nsw-docs__guideline">
    <div class="nsw-docs__guideline--do">Do</div>
    <p>Use a horizontal bar chart that starts at zero with direct labels and a clear timeframe.</p>
    <div class="nsw-m-top-sm">
      <canvas id="example1Good" height="180" role="img" aria-label="Horizontal bar chart starting at zero with clear labels."></canvas>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li>Start the axis at zero or clearly indicate truncation.</li>
      <li>Include timeframe and unit in the title.</li>
      <li>Keep labels readable and aligned.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>Example 2: Colour-only differentiation</h3>
<div class="nsw-grid nsw-m-top-sm">
  <div class="nsw-col nsw-col-sm-6 nsw-docs__guideline">
    <div class="nsw-docs__guideline--dont">Don't</div>
    <p>Stacked bar uses red and green only, with no labels and low contrast.</p>
    <div class="nsw-m-top-sm">
      <canvas id="example2Bad" height="180" role="img" aria-label="Stacked bar chart using red and green only with no labels."></canvas>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li>Relies on colour alone to communicate meaning.</li>
      <li>Insufficient contrast for some users.</li>
      <li>No direct labels or markers.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="nsw-col nsw-col-sm-6 nsw-docs__guideline">
    <div class="nsw-docs__guideline--do">Do</div>
    <p>Use accessible colours, clear contrast, and a supporting table for labels.</p>
    <div class="nsw-m-top-sm">
      <canvas id="example2Good" height="180" role="img" aria-label="Stacked bar chart with accessible colours and clear labels."></canvas>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide labels in a table, not colour alone.</li>
      <li>Meet WCAG contrast requirements.</li>
      <li>Keep the chart clear in greyscale and colour-blind testing.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="nsw-table-responsive nsw-m-top-sm">
      <table class="nsw-table">
        <caption class="sr-only">Resolution by quarter</caption>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Quarter</th>
            <th scope="col">Resolved on time</th>
            <th scope="col">Resolved late</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">Q1</th>
            <td>120</td>
            <td>30</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">Q2</th>
            <td>140</td>
            <td>25</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">Q3</th>
            <td>110</td>
            <td>40</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">Q4</th>
            <td>150</td>
            <td>20</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>Example 3: Tooltip-only values</h3>
<div class="nsw-grid nsw-m-top-sm">
  <div class="nsw-col nsw-col-sm-6 nsw-docs__guideline">
    <div class="nsw-docs__guideline--dont">Don't</div>
    <p>Line chart shows values only on hover with no table or summary.</p>
    <div class="nsw-m-top-sm">
      <canvas id="example3Bad" height="180" role="img" aria-label="Line chart with values available only on hover."></canvas>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li>Keyboard and touch users cannot access key values.</li>
      <li>No text alternative for screen readers.</li>
      <li>Users cannot verify exact values.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="nsw-col nsw-col-sm-6 nsw-docs__guideline">
    <div class="nsw-docs__guideline--do">Do</div>
    <p>Include a summary and a semantic table for the same data.</p>
    <div class="nsw-m-top-sm">
      <canvas id="example3Good" height="180" role="img" aria-label="Line chart with a summary and data table."></canvas>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li>Use summary text for the key insight.</li>
      <li>Provide precise values in a table.</li>
      <li>Keep interactions keyboard accessible.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="nsw-m-top-sm"><strong>Summary:</strong> Applications rose steadily from January to May, with a small drop in June.</p>
    <div class="nsw-table-responsive nsw-m-top-sm">
