  </div>
</div>


<h2 id="review-checklist">Review checklist</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Does the chart match the user task?</li>
  <li>Is it the simplest suitable type?</li>
  <li>Is contrast sufficient?</li>
  <li>Is colour supported by other markers?</li>
  <li>Is there a semantic table?</li>
  <li>Is keyboard access supported?</li>
  <li>Does it work at 200 percent zoom?</li>
  <li>Are units and source clearly stated?</li>
</ul>
<p>If any answer is no, revise before release.</p>


<h2 id="code-implementation">Implementation examples</h2>
<p class="intro">
  The examples below show how to apply NSW palette and typography using Chart.js. Use them as a reference if you are using Chart.js or a similar library, and adapt the same principles for other tools.
</p>
<p>On this page, the live chart canvases are rendered from the docs script using the canvas IDs shown above.</p>

<h3>Installing and usage (Chart.js)</h3>
<p>Follow the <a href="https://www.chartjs.org/docs/latest/getting-started/installation.html" target="_blank">Chart.js installation instructions</a> in their documentation.</p>
<p>Once installed, follow the normal <a href="https://www.chartjs.org/docs/latest/getting-started/usage.html" target="_blank">Chart.js usage instructions</a> and apply the settings below to align with NSW branding and accessibility expectations.</p>

<h3>Theming with the NSW Government Palette</h3>
<p>Use the design guidance above to decide which colours your chart or graph should use. You can access the full palette via JavaScript.</p>
<p>First, set fonts and a default theme. These will be the default colours for your charts and graphs, but you can override them if needed.</p>

{{#>_docs-example hidden="true" open="true" code="html"}}
<script>
const { getNswChartPalette } = window.NSWChartUtilities;
const palette = getNswChartPalette();

Chart.defaults.backgroundColor = [
  palette.blue02,
  palette.red02,
  palette.yellow02,
  palette.green02,
  palette.purple02,
  palette.orange02,
  palette.fuchsia02,
];
Chart.defaults.font.family = "'Public Sans'";
Chart.defaults.font.size = 14;
Chart.defaults.font.weight = 400;
<\/script>
{{/_docs-example}}

<h3>Setting colours for a specific graph</h3>
<p>You can theme each chart or graph individually.</p>

{{#>_docs-example hidden="true" open="true" code="html"}}
<script>
const { getNswChartPalette } = window.NSWChartUtilities;
const palette = getNswChartPalette();

const data = {
  labels: [
    'Item 1',
    'Item 2',
    'Item 3'
  ],
  datasets: [{
    label: 'Example Dataset',
    data: [300, 50, 100],
    backgroundColor: [
      palette.blue01,
      palette.blue02,
      palette.blue03
    ],
    hoverOffset: 4
  }]
};

var myChart = new Chart(
  document.getElementById('myChart'), {
    type: 'pie',
    data: data,
  }
);
<\/script>
{{/_docs-example}}

